{
  "name": "Folk Hero",
  "type": "background",
  "img": "icons/skills/social/intimidation-impressing.webp",
  "system": {
    "description": "<p>You were born to a commoner family, but some event earned you fame. You&rsquo;re admired locally, and tales of your deeds have reached the far corners of the world.</p><p>Did you win your fame by battling an oppressive tyrant? Saving your village from a monster? Or by something more prosaic like winning a wrestling bout or a pie-eating contest?</p><hr><p><strong>Ability Score Increases:</strong>&nbsp;+1 to Constitution and one other ability score.</p><p><strong>Skill Proficiencies:&nbsp;</strong>Survival, and either Animal Handling or Nature.</p><p><strong>Tool Proficiencies:</strong>&nbsp;One type of artisan&rsquo;s tools, one vehicle.</p><p><strong>Suggested Equipment (Cost 2&ndash;31 gold):&nbsp;</strong>Any artisan&rsquo;s tools except alchemist&rsquo;s supplies, common clothes.</p><p><strong><em>Feature: Local Fame</em></strong><strong>.</strong>&nbsp;Unless you conceal your identity, you&rsquo;re universally recognized and admired near the site of your exploits. You and your companions are treated to a moderate lifestyle in any settlement within 100 miles of your Prestige Center.&nbsp;</p><p><strong><em>Adventures and Advancement</em></strong><strong>.&nbsp;</strong>Common folk come to you with all sorts of problems. If you fought an oppressive regime, they bring you tales of injustice. If you fought a monster, they seek you out with monster problems. If you solve many such predicaments, you become universally famous, gaining the benefits of your Local Fame feature in every settled land.</p><h3><strong>FOLK HERO CONNECTIONS</strong></h3><ol><li>The bard whose song made you legendary and who wants a sequel.</li><li>Your friend, a traveling merchant whose caravan spreads your fame.</li><li>A deadly enemy: the heir of the oppressive noble you killed.</li><li>A deadly enemy: the mother of the monster you killed.</li><li>A deadly enemy: the leader of the bandits you defeated.</li><li>A deadly enemy: the tyrant you robbed.</li><li>A kid who wants to follow your footsteps into danger.</li><li>The jealous rival who wants to best your monster-slaying prowess, daring deeds, prize pie recipe, or whatever else made your famous.</li><li>A secret admirer: the heir or heiress of the oppressive noble you defeated.</li><li>The retired adventurer who trained you and is now in a bit of trouble.</li></ol><hr><h3><strong>FOLK HERO MEMENTOS</strong></h3><ol><li>The mask you used to conceal your identity while fighting oppression (you are only recognized as a folk hero while wearing the mask).</li><li>A necklace bearing a horn, tooth, or claw from the monster you defeated.</li><li>A ring given to you by the dead relative whose death you avenged.</li><li>The weapon you wrestled from the leader of the raid on your village.</li><li>The trophy, wrestling belt, silver pie plate, or other prize marking you as the county champion.</li><li>The famous scar you earned in your struggle against your foe.</li><li>The signature weapon which provides you with your nickname.</li><li>The injury or physical difference by which your admirers and foes recognize you.</li><li>The signal whistle or instrument which you used to summon allies and spook enemies.</li><li>Copies of the ballads and poems written in your honor.</li></ol>",
